<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="willing-adj">willing <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'wɪlɪŋ/    美 /'wɪlɪŋ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>愿意的；乐意的：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>be willing to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Successful people are always willing to do every little thing well.
成功的人总是愿意做好每一件小事。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If we are willing to learn, the opportunities are everywhere.
如果我们愿意学习，到处都是机会。</p><footer>2019 天津</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(人、行为等) 自发的；出于自愿的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a willing helper
自愿帮助别人的人</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>willingly  /'wɪlɪŋli/ adv <br />
willingness /'wɪlɪŋnəs/ n [U]   </p></div>